"Troms\u00f8 Farvehandel HAFA AS har sendt en henvendelse ang\u00e5ende oppf\u00f8ring av en rullestolrampe ved Storgata 57. Kommunen informerer at tiltaket er s\u00f8knadspliktig og krever tegninger og situasjonsplan. Det kan ogs\u00e5 v\u00e6re n\u00f8dvendig med en uttalelse fra fylkeskommunen og \u00e5 se p\u00e5 reguleringsplanen. Kommunen gir ogs\u00e5 informasjon om s\u00f8knadsprosessen og byggtekniske krav. Vedtak og dokumenter kan finnes p\u00e5 kommunens nettsider. Signert av Marianne Melbye, ingeni\u00f8r ved Seksjon for byutvikling, Byggesak.A business in Troms\u00f8 requested approval for a wheelchair ramp at their property. After reviewing the drawings and consulting with the cultural environment adviser, it was determined that the ramp does not require a permit. However, it was emphasized that the design of the ramp should be in line with the building's aesthetics. The use of a metal grate ramp was discouraged. Additional guidance on the design can be obtained from Bodil Ruud.The email thread discusses the construction of a wheelchair ramp at Storgata 57 in Troms\u00f8. The sender is seeking approval from the Building Department of Troms\u00f8 municipality, as they are the owners of the sidewalk where the ramp will be placed. The sender includes details about the dimensions of the ramp and previous communication with Kim-Runar Dalberg Olsen regarding the project."